<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-05-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="654" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-05-07"><hi rend="italic">May 7,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I have received 5 o’clock p.m. from admiral commanding the answer to my
                            communication of the 30th in regard to the American citizens captured on
                                <hi rend="italic">Competitor</hi>. He replies seventh article of the
                            treaty 1795 and the protocol do not apply to them as they are not
                            residents in accordance with law relating to foreigners and they are to
                            be tried by summary court martial. I am preparing answer and protest in
                            accordance with your telegram 2d instant.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>